Package: inequantiles
Title: Quantile-Based Inequality Measures for Survey Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Silvia", "Scarpa", , "silvia.scarpa@unimore.it", 
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4003-1621")),
    person("Stefan", "Sperlich", email = "Stefan.Sperlich@unige.ch", 
    role = "aut"))
Description: Estimates quantiles and quantile-based inequality indicators,
    such as the quantile ratio index, quintile share ratio, Palma
    ratio, and percentile ratios, from complex survey data.
    Influence functions are provided for linearization-based
    variance estimation, along with a rescaled bootstrap method
    for complex sampling designs. Estimation of the quantile ratio
    index and Gini coefficient from grouped data is also supported.
    See Scarpa et al. (2025) <doi:10.1093/jssam/smaf024> for details.
